{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "# mosum.py: user guide\n",
    "\n",
    "## Installation\n",
    "`(.venv) $ pip install mosum`\n",
    "\n",
    "## Generating data\n",
    "We can simulate data from a mean-change model with `testdata`.\n",
    "The simulated data is stored in `x`, and the signal in `mu`."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import mosum\n",
    "sim = mosum.testData(\"blocks\")\n",
    "x = sim[\"x\"]\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "pd.Series(x).plot()\n",
    "plt.plot(sim[\"mu\"], '-', lw=2)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## MOSUM procedure\n",
    "\n",
    "The function `mosum` uses a single bandwidth to detect changes.\n",
    "This returns an object with `plot`, `print`, and `summary` methods.\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ms = mosum.mosum(x, G = 20)\n",
    "ms.plot()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ms.plot(display=\"mosum\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "change points detected with bandwidths (20,20) at alpha = 0.1 according to eta-criterion with eta = 0.4 and mosum variance estimate:\n",

      "0   203      20       20    0.017  1.517\n",

      "5  1658      20       20    0.001  1.882\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ms.print()"

    "collapsed": false

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Multiscale MOSUM procedure with bottom-up merging\n",
    "\n",
    "The function `multiscale_bottomUp` runs the MOSUM procedure with multiple bandwidths, merging these from smallest to largest.\n",
    "Again, this returns an object with `plot`, `print`, and `summary` methods.\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%%capture --no-display\n",
    "ms_multi = mosum.multiscale_bottomUp(x, G = [10,20,40])\n",
    "ms_multi.plot()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## 3D visualisation\n",
    "\n",
    "We can visualise in 3D the MOSUM detector at a range of scales, with the heights and colours of the detector corresponding to the size."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "outputs": [

     "metadata": {},

   ],

    "mosum.persp3D_multiscaleMosum(x)"
